@startuml fig-tcp-sack
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Selective Acknowledgement (SACK) — Retransmission Example

participant "Sender" as S #FFE0B2
participant "Receiver" as R #C8E6C9

S -> R : Segment 1 (bytes 0–999)
S -> R : Segment 2 (bytes 1000–1999)
S -[#E53935]x R : <color:#E53935>Segment 3 (bytes 2000–2999) — LOST</color>
S -> R : Segment 4 (bytes 3000–3999)
S -> R : Segment 5 (bytes 4000–4999)

|||

R -[#1565C0]> S : ACK = 2000\nSACK blocks: [3000–5000)

note right of R #FFF9C4
  Cumulative ACK: next expected = 2000
  SACK reports: bytes 3000–4999 received
  Only segment 3 needs retransmission
end note

|||

S -[#FF9800]> R : Retransmit segment 3 (bytes 2000–2999)
R -[#43A047]> S : ACK = 5000 (all data received)

legend right
  SACK reduces unnecessary retransmissions.
  The receiver reports non-contiguous ranges
  so the sender retransmits only the gap.
  Requires SACK Permitted negotiation
  during the three-way handshake.
endlegend
@enduml
